Acer’s Aspire 5 laptops have been updated to include Intel’s new 11th-generation processors as well as exciting new colours. This makes these devices the perfect choice for anyone who wants a laptop with the latest technology and also looks great. Intel’s 11th-generation laptop processors offer significantly improved performance over their predecessors. The updated Acer Aspire 5 range available in South Africa comprises six laptops which use a variety of these new processors – ranging from the affordable yet potent Intel Core i3-1115G4, to the high-end Intel Core i7-1165G7. All are paired with 8GB of RAM, which is more than enough for your home and office needs, as well as a speedy 256GB SSD. The one exception to this is the top-of-the-range i7 model, which offers 512GB SSD storage. The Aspire 5 laptops also come with Windows 10 installed and offer crisp 14-inch Full HD displays which are great for streaming the latest series, holding a Teams call, or working on your company’s software. Additionally, Wi-Fi 6 connectivity and Gigabit Ethernet ensures that you get the best possible Internet connection at all times. The new Acer Aspire 5 series is available from Acer’s local online store from just R10,499. These laptops are available in classy new colours, with the different models available in the following colours: Specifications and photos of the new Acer Aspire 5 range are posted below. <img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-383678" src="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/Aspire-Image-1.jpg" alt="" width="601" height="334" /> <img class="size-full wp-image-383680 aligncenter" src="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/Aspire-Image-2.jpg" alt="" width="601" height="334" /> This article was published in partnership with Acer.